name: Joram
note: Bouldering (2.5h): was trying to top 4 new mint routes (5B-5C). Managed to top one (5B), nearly get another. And I got stuck on one last one for over an hour. I set my goal to not leave before I got it. I must have tried it 50 times getting people to help me, watch, pass me over and over. My heart was pounding on every climb, I nearly had it. Muscles flooded with acid, palms sweating. I managed to squeeze out just a last bit of energy and I hit it well (5B+). A big smile ensued. Ha, take that sisyphus!
